title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1980-10-13
description:
Set 1

On The Road Again, Bird Song, El Paso, To Lay Me Down, Heaven Help The Fool, Jack A Roe, The Race is On, Deep Elem Blues-> Ripple

Set 2

Sugaree-> Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, CC Rider, Big Railroad Blues, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Deal

Set 3

Cold Rain & Snow, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> He's Gone-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Casey Jones

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text: Stella Blue This Stella Blue is outrageously gorgeous!

Thanks Alan (This is the most complete and *best version on the archive). Look, I’m going to be real with you: I was born in 92, I’d like to think I’ve listened to my fair share of the dead… as such, I’ve developed the habit of looking for Mr. Miller’s SBD first… read the tapper notes and you will see all the same names. Thank you for your hard work Mr. Alan. 

Alan, giving credit to Mr. Miller is why I gave it it a try (plus I was trying to find the Heaven Help the Fool) I listen to last year on TDIGDH. 

Per the taper notes first time the complete set has been put together (Nov ‘18 or 16, on phone can’t check). 

Beautiful. 

If you’re on your journey of listening to TDIGDH, don’t skip this show, and there is no other recording you should listen to (I’m going to put this at the top of the comment as well). 

I hope you enjoy! Especially those that are primiarly primordial dead fans. There are a few shows that, ehhhem, show you the light…

I just wanted to write this because I almost skipped this recording and missed out. 


*only my personal opinion.
